The file notascript.txt needs to be transformed to become
a valid script. Perform the following transformations:
- Replace any "ZZZ" with "1"
- Sort the results
- Split each line into two columns (tab as delimiter) and keep only the 2nd column
- Save the final results as a new file testscript.sh
- Make the script executable and run it




After running the script, it updated the timestamp one of the files within the "script"
folder (and subfolder). Use the find command to find any files that have been modified
in the last five minutes - assuming you ran the script within the last 5 minutes.































Answers below -- scroll down to see.....
































sed 's/ZZZ/1/g' input.txt | sort | cut -f2


find . -type f -mmin -5
